S3 is an object storage service in AWS used to store files, images, backups, logs, and static assets.

Objects = files + metadata

Stored in buckets

Highly durable (99.999999999% â€“ â€œ11 9sâ€)


2ï¸âƒ£ Key Features

	1ï¸âƒ£ Durability & Reliability

	Stores objects across multiple AZs automatically

	2ï¸âƒ£ Scalability

	Handles virtually unlimited storage

	Auto scales with usage

	3ï¸âƒ£ Security

	IAM policies & bucket policies

	Encryption at rest (SSE) and in transit (HTTPS)

	4ï¸âƒ£ Versioning

	Keep multiple versions of the same object

	Useful for recovery

	5ï¸âƒ£ Lifecycle Management

	Auto move objects to cheaper storage (S3 Glacier)


3ï¸âƒ£ Use Cases

	Static assets for web apps (images, CSS, JS)

	Backups & logs

	Data lake / big data storage

	Hosting simple static websites

