ğŸ”¹ 1ï¸âƒ£ What is an S3 Bucket?

A bucket is a container in S3 where you store your objects.

Think of it like a folder in the cloud, but:

Buckets have globally unique names (across all AWS accounts)

You can set permissions, policies, and region per bucket

Example:

Bucket name: myapp-uploads

Region: ap-south-1

ğŸ”¹ 2ï¸âƒ£ What is an S3 Object?

An object is the actual file stored in a bucket.

Objects can be any file: image, video, JSON, CSV, logs

Each object has:

Data (the content)

Metadata (info about the object, e.g., size, content-type)

Key (unique identifier)

Example:

File: profile_pic.png

Stored in bucket: myapp-uploads

ğŸ”¹ 3ï¸âƒ£ What is the Key?

The key is the unique name for an object in a bucket.

Combined with the bucket name â†’ unique address of the object

Example:

Bucket: myapp-uploads
Key: users/123/profile_pic.png


Full S3 URL:

https://myapp-uploads.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/users/123/profile_pic.png

ğŸ”¹ 4ï¸âƒ£ Quick Analogy
Concept	Analogy
Bucket	Folder / container
Object	File inside the folder
Key	File path / filename
ğŸ”¹ 5ï¸âƒ£ Interview-Perfect Answer (Memorize)

â€œIn S3, a bucket is a container for storing objects. An object is the file stored in the bucket, and each object has a key, which is its unique name or path inside the bucket.â€



