What â€œObjects are immutableâ€ means

Once you upload an object to S3, you cannot modify it in place.

If you want to â€œchangeâ€ it, you have to upload a new version or overwrite the existing object.

S3 stores each version as a separate object if versioning is enabled.

Example

Bucket: myapp-uploads
Key: users/123/profile_pic.png

1ï¸âƒ£ Upload profile_pic.png â†’ S3 stores it
2ï¸âƒ£ You want to change it â†’ edit locally and upload again to same key
3ï¸âƒ£ Old file replaced (or stored as old version if versioning enabled)

Why this matters

No partial updates â†’ simpler storage system

High durability & consistency

Works well with cloud architecture and multiple AZs

ğŸ”¹ Optional: Versioning

If versioning enabled, S3 keeps all versions

You can recover previous versions if needed

Example:

users/123/profile_pic.png â†’ v1
users/123/profile_pic.png â†’ v2

